reviews.review_text:
Eighth Days Between 8/41: Terrapin (16:43)->Drumz (22:36)->INAM (4:55)->Days (9:30)->NFA

Short first set, but what's there is good. Yes, the Jack Straw is slow going at first and the set picks up steam with the Loser... I always dig the new arrangement on It's All Over Now. Even Phil sounds good on Tom Thumb's Blues, one of his few tunes that I can (honestly) stomach. Bird Songs gets out there. Highlight of the night, no question, is in the second set: The whole jam suite from Terrapin through Days is huge.
